quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  92,1,And (by) the night when it envelops
  92,2,And (by) the day when it manifests itself
  92,3,"And (by) That (i.e., the present life) which created the male and the female"
  92,4,Surely your endeavor is indeed to diverse (ends)
  92,5,"So, as for him who gives, and is pious"
  92,6,And sincerely (believes) in the fairest (reward)
  92,7,Then We will soon ease him to the Easiest
  92,8,"And as for him who is miserly, and thinks himself self-sufficient"
  92,9,And cries lies to the fairest (reward)
  92,10,Then We will soon ease him to the (great) Difficulty
  92,11,And in no way will his wealth avail him when he topples (to death)
  92,12,Surely upon Us (rests) indeed the guidance
  92,13,"And surely to Us (belong) indeed the Hereafter and the First (i.e., the present life)"
  92,14,So I have warned you of a Fire that blazes fiercely
  92,15,Whereat none except the most wretched will be roasted
  92,16,(He) who cried lies and turned away
  92,17,And which the most pious will soon be made to avoid
  92,18,(He) who brings (forth) his wealth to cleanse himself
  92,19,And in no way has anyone in his presence any favor to be recompensed
  92,20,"Except for seeking the Face of his Lord, The Most Exalted"
  92,21,And indeed he will eventually be satisfied